CVE-2025-52999: jackson-core nesting depth DoS (StackOverflowError)

Backport of upstream commit 74584f6f0f73a9124d0ae265c57b71fd734f2684
(PR #943, "apply constraint to nesting depth") to jackson-core 2.12.5.

The 2.12.x branch predates the StreamReadConstraints infrastructure
introduced in 2.15. This minimized backport tracks nesting depth on
JsonReadContext / JsonStreamContext and enforces a hard-coded maximum
of 1000 (matching the upstream default) via new helper methods
createChildArrayContext / createChildObjectContext on ParserBase. Each
parser implementation (ReaderBasedJsonParser, UTF8StreamJsonParser,
UTF8DataInputJsonParser, NonBlockingJsonParserBase) is updated to
route child-context creation through these helpers, so deeply nested
JSON now throws JsonParseException("Depth (N) exceeds the maximum
allowed nesting depth (1000)") instead of crashing the JVM thread
with StackOverflowError.

A regression test (ArrayParsingTest.testDeepNesting) is added,
adapted from the upstream PR #943 fix. The test uses Java 6
compatible try/finally rather than try-with-resources because
jackson-core 2.12.x targets -source 1.6 / -target 1.6.

Origin: backport of https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-core/commit/74584f6f0f73a9124d0ae265c57b71fd734f2684
Bug: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-core/pull/943
CVE: CVE-2025-52999

